| US, Asia, Europe Ceding Web Dominance                              |
|   from the hello-new-friends dept.                                 |
|   posted by Zonk on Saturday April 14, @21:39 (The Internet)       |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/14/2352203              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "A new study shows that presence of the [0]US,
[1]Asia, and [2]Western European countries on the web is strongly
declining. [3]Newly internet-empowered countries are booming; many
geographical regions are showing exponential growth, including [4]Eastern
Europe and [5]South America. Chris Harrison explains: 'Countries that
have never been able to place a website in the top 500 are now pushing
dozens of established websites out of this prestigious list. This trend
is both recent (within the last two years) and accelerating.
Interestingly, Asia is seeing it's presence eroded the fastest,
especially China.'"

Discuss this story at:
    http://slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/14/2352203

Links:
    0. http://www.chrisharrison.net/projects/trafficvis/usdomains.html
    1. http://www.chrisharrison.net/projects/trafficvis/asiadomains.html
    2. http://www.chrisharrison.net/projects/trafficvis/westeurodomains.html
    3. http://www.chrisharrison.net/projects/trafficvis/index.html
    4. http://www.chrisharrison.net/projects/trafficvis/easteurodomains.html
    5. http://www.chrisharrison.net/projects/trafficvis/southlatinamerica.html


