+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Norway Liberal Party Wants Legal File Sharing                      |
|   from the pirate-party-platform dept.                             |
|   posted by kdawson on Sunday April 15, @19:04 (The Internet)      |
|   http://politics.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/15/1950200     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]dot-magnon writes "[1]The Liberal Party of Norway (Venstre) passed a
[2]unanimous resolution that advocates legal file sharing. The party
wants to legalise sharing of any copyrighted material for non-commercial
use. It also proposes a ban on DRM technology, free sampling of other
artists' material, and shortening the life span of copyright. The Liberal
Party is the first Norwegian political party, and the first European
mainstream political party, to advocate file sharing. The Liberal Party's
youth wing proposed the resolution."

Discuss this story at:
    http://politics.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/15/1950200

Links:
    0. http://magnon.wordpress.com/
    1. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Venstre_(Norway)
    2. http://www.uv.no/politics/translated-items/culture-wants-to-be-free?set_language=en



